headline: How The Evolving Story For Galaxy Digital NasdaqGS:GLXY Is Reshaping Analyst Valuations
summary: Why Galaxy Digital’s Price Target Just Got Recut Galaxy Digital’s latest fair value estimate has shifted down from about US$47.82 to about US$43.18, as analysts reset their expectations around how quickly the business can grow and how much risk they are willing to price in. Revenue growth assumptions have moved from about 74.61% to about 14.60%. The discount rate used in several models now sits closer to 9.66% instead of 9.00%, capturing a higher required return for owning the stock. Stay...

headline: Why The Narrative Around Waste Connections WCN Is Shifting As Analysts Reassess Growth And Risks
summary: Waste Connections' fair value estimate has shifted only slightly, moving from about US$204.46 to roughly US$204.25 per share. This reflects a more cautious tone in recent Street research rather than a wholesale rethink of the story. headline: What Catalysts Could Shift The Home Depot (HD) Story After Mixed Analyst Reviews
summary: Home Depot’s fair value estimate has barely moved, with the analyst shifting from about US$394.12 to about US$394.09 per share, while the discount rate and long term revenue growth assumptions are also only slightly adjusted. This tiny reset reflects a more mixed research backdrop, where some firms are trimming targets on softer Q3 results and guidance, and others are still leaning into the longer term story around pro and wholesale growth.
